                        <div class="item">
                            <a class="image" href="../horse-detail.html"><img src="../img/sale-horses/sierra-broncos-breezy-342x300.jpg"></a>
                            <h2>Sierra Broncos Breezy</h2>
                            <p>color: <strong>Buckskin</strong><br>dob: <strong>5/15/2008</strong></p>
                            <p class="price">$3000</p>
                            <p>Breezy is a true miniature horse in every way. She is small, refined, has attitude and looks like a little Arabian. She is so adorable with her large eyes and pretty face. Her pedigree has Champions everywhere. This mare is very correct and a daughter of our senior stallion Just Bronco. Bronco made an enormous impact on our breeding program here at Sierra Ranch and very few foals are available by Bronco.</p>
                            <p>sire: <strong>Just Bronco 28.50”</strong><br>dam: <strong>Sierra Golds Dances With Wind 28.50”</strong></p>
                        </div> <!--// .item -->

                        <div class="item">
                            <a class="image slideshow" href="../horse-detail.html">
                                <img src="../img/sale-horses/sierra-golds-american-treasure-342x256.jpg">
                                <img src="../img/sale-horses/sierra-golds-american-treasure-342x256.jpg">
                                <img src="../img/sale-horses/sierra-golds-american-treasure-342x256.jpg">
                                <img src="../img/sale-horses/sierra-golds-american-treasure-342x256.jpg">
                                <span></span>
                            </a>
                            <h2>Sierra Golds American Treasure</h2>
                            <p>color: <strong>Palomino Pinto</strong><br>dob: <strong>4/18/2003</strong></p>
                            <p class="price">$3000</p>
                            <p>his stunning mare is a daughter of our well known stallion Gold Dust. On her dam's side, she goes back to Scott Creek High Roller and Little Kings Napoleon. She won many Supreme Championships when she was shown as a 3 year old, and has now gone on to be a wonderful broodmare. She's proven, with 3 foals on the ground. Her gorgeous golden palomino pinto markings, combined with her correct and refined conformation, make her the total package.</p>
                            <p>sire: <strong>Mcarthurs Imperial Gold Dust 33.00”</strong></p>
                        </div> <!--// .item -->

                        <div class="item">
                            <a class="image slideshow" href="../horse-detail.html">
                                <img src="../img/sale-horses/sierra-bronco-kb-destiny-342x247.jpg">
                                <img src="../img/sale-horses/sierra-bronco-kb-destiny-342x247.jpg">
                                <img src="../img/sale-horses/sierra-bronco-kb-destiny-342x247.jpg">
                                <img src="../img/sale-horses/sierra-bronco-kb-destiny-342x247.jpg">
                                <span></span>
                            </a>
                            <h2>Sierra Broncos KB Destiny</h2>
                            <p>color: <strong>Bay Pinto</strong><br>dob: <strong>5/23/2008</strong></p>
                            <p class="price">$3500</p>
                            <p>Breezy is a true miniature horse in every way. She is small, refined, has attitude and looks like a little Arabian. She is so adorable with her large eyes and pretty face. Her pedigree has Champions everywhere. This mare is very correct and a daughter of our senior stallion Just Bronco. Bronco made an enormous impact on our breeding program here at Sierra Ranch and very few foals are available by Bronco.</p>
                            <p>sire: <strong>Just Bronco 28.50”</strong><br>dam: <strong>Sierra Golds Dances With Wind 28.50”</strong></p>
                        </div> <!--// .item -->

                        <div class="item">
                            <a class="noimage" href="../horse-detail.html"></a>
                            <h2>Sierras Baha Rose</h2>
                            <p>color: <strong>Black</strong><br>dob: <strong>3/21/1992</strong></p>
                            <p class="price">$1200</p>
                            <p>Baha is a gorgeous, tiny, refined mare that has been one of our main broodmares here at Sierra Ranch. She is the daughter of Sierras Guns and Roses, a stallion who was exported to New Zealand. Guns and Roses went on to sire more Supreme Champions than any other stallion in New Zealand at the time. We have retained three of Baha’s daughters for future breeding. Baha is now looking for that forever home that will appreciate her for the rest of her life. She would make a great pet, or could still be used as a broodmare.</p>
                            <p>sire: <strong>Sierras Guns And Roses 29.50”</strong></p>
